Burudihi is a medium size village located in Badampahar Block of Mayurbhanj district, Orissa with total 101 families residing. The Burudihi village has population of 449 of which 230 are males while 219 are females as per Population Census 2011.

In Burudihi village population of children with age 0-6 is 65 which makes up 14.48 % of total population of village. Average Sex Ratio of Burudihi village is 952 which is lower than Orissa state average of 979. Child Sex Ratio for the Burudihi as per census is 1097, higher than Orissa average of 941.

Burudihi village has lower literacy rate compared to Orissa. In 2011, literacy rate of Burudihi village was 64.32 % compared to 72.87 % of Orissa. In Burudihi Male literacy stands at 82.91 % while female literacy rate was 44.32 %.

